            <title>[MNG-1927] ${project.build.directory} different in M2.0 &amp; M2.0.1</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-1927</link>
                <project id="12316922" key="MNG">Maven (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From Jens:&lt;br/&gt;
In Maven 2.0 the value containes the whole absolute path to the target&lt;br/&gt;
dir.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;C:\windows\system32\target&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With Maven 2.0.1 only:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;target\&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Note: I was unable to reproduce this against 2.0, instead getting ${project.build.directory} verbatim, but I believe it should be an absolute path)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
